Your hardware

The Pre-Frontal Cortex

This is the bit that tries to concentrate on what you need to get done. It keeps your focus on planning and tries to direct you away from those 'pesky' emotions.

The Limbic Brain

This is your brain's bodyguard. Always on the lookout for you, it's the bit that kicks your body into high gear when needed. Heart rate, breathing, sleep, appetite these are the levers it pulls when danger or stress raise their ugly heads!

The Autonomic Nervous System

That's the 'ANS' to you and me! It connects the limbic brain to your heart and does its job in 2 ways:

 

  • The sympathetic system: Adrenaline and Noradrenaline turn your 'fight' or 'flight' response on and off.  Think of it as your accelerator (vroooom!)
  • The parasympathetic system: This is the brake. It'll calm you down and make you relax, putting you into the 'rest and repair' state we all need now and again (aaah, that's better!)
